{"ts":"2026-04-28T12:00:00Z","agent":"ALPHA","soul_name":"GrittyGrad","issue":"trios#143","task":"ATTENTION_BACKWARD_V5","status":"REGRESS","phi_step":"EXPERIENCE","triplet":"RAIL=experience @ project=trios-trainer-igla service=v5-attn-backward sha=cd91c45 ts=2026-04-28T12:00:00Z","evidence":"v5 results WORSE than v4. seed43=2.6186(+0.43) seed44=2.6038(+0.40) seed45=2.4834(+0.29). Root cause: removed attn_down projection from gradient path. attn_down projected hidden(828)->d_model(64) and its gradient flowed correctly in v4. v5 replaced attn_down with raw embeddings fed to attention as sequence. The attention backward adds gradients for wq/wk/wv/wo (32K params) but lost the attn_down gradient path (53K params). The raw embeddings are not learnable through attention (they are shared with embed table). Hypothesis: need BOTH attn_down sequence AND attention backward. Also seq_len=8 may be too long for the current d_model=64 — attention dilutes signal across 8 positions when model only has 64 dim to represent them."}
{"ts":"2026-04-28T12:05:00Z","agent":"ALPHA","soul_name":"GrittyGrad","issue":"trios#143","task":"V4_BASELINE_CONFIRMED","status":"DONE","phi_step":"EXPERIENCE","triplet":"RAIL=experience @ project=trios-trainer-igla service=v4-baseline sha=cd91c45 ts=2026-04-28T12:05:00Z","evidence":"v4 (no attention backward, seq_len=1, attn_down projected): seed43=2.1919 seed44=2.2024 seed45=2.1944. avg=2.1962. 81K steps, h=828, attn=2L, lr=0.003, adamw. Best single run: seed43=2.18 in earlier V3 corrected-gradient runs. Architecture: ngram(6)+2L_hybrid_attn+ReLU2. Params=338K."}
{"ts":"2026-04-28T12:10:00Z","agent":"ALPHA","soul_name":"GrittyGrad","issue":"trios#143","task":"ATTENTION_BACKWARD_IMPL","status":"DONE","phi_step":"EXPERIENCE","triplet":"RAIL=experience @ project=trios-trainer-igla service=model_hybrid_attn sha=cd91c45 ts=2026-04-28T12:10:00Z","evidence":"Implemented full backward pass in model_hybrid_attn.rs: AttentionCache struct stores Q/K/V/softmax_weights/pre_wo/residuals/LN outputs for both layers. AttentionGrads struct has gwq/gwk/gwv/gwo/gwq2/gwk2/gwv2/gwo2/d_input. backward_single_layer: d_out->d_attn_pre_wo via wo^T, softmax backward, Q/K/V gradient, input projection gradient via wq^T+wk^2+wv^T. 2-layer backward: LN->residual->attn_backward->LN->residual->attn_backward. Helpers: matmul_transpose_a (a^T@b), matmul_transpose_b (a@b^T), layer_norm_rows_backward. 468 lib tests GREEN."}
{"ts":"2026-04-28T12:15:00Z","agent":"ALPHA","soul_name":"GrittyGrad","issue":"trios#143","task":"MUON_FALSIFIED_FINAL","status":"FALSIFIED","phi_step":"VERDICT","triplet":"RAIL=experience @ project=trios-trainer-igla service=p1-muon-lab sha=cd91c45 ts=2026-04-28T12:15:00Z","evidence":"P1 Muon Lab FINAL verdict: AdamW control BPB=2.4819 @ 12K steps. Muon NS-1 BPB=2.5906 (+0.11 WORSE). MuonCwd killed before completion. Muon optimizer does not beat AdamW on this architecture (338K params, char-level, tiny_shakespeare). Decision: stick with AdamW for all future experiments. Root cause hypothesis: Muon's orthogonalization works well for large matrices (FineWeb-scale) but hurts on small 828x64 projection matrices where AdamW's per-element adaptation is more efficient."}
{"ts":"2026-04-28T12:20:00Z","agent":"ALPHA","soul_name":"GrittyGrad","issue":"trios#143","task":"LESSON_SUMMARY_20260428","status":"DONE","phi_step":"REPORT","triplet":"RAIL=experience @ project=trios-trainer-igla service=meta sha=cd91c45 ts=2026-04-28T12:20:00Z","evidence":"KEY LESSONS: (1) Attention backward alone does not help if you remove an existing working gradient path (attn_down). Always measure before removing. (2) seq_len>1 with raw embeddings does not work because embeddings are shared params with the ngram path — attention gradients fight with ngram gradients on the same embed vectors. (3) The v4 attn_down projection (828->64) was actually providing useful learned features, not just random noise. (4) 468 tests pass after adding backward — implementation is correct but the architecture choice was wrong. (5) Gap to target 1.50 remains 0.68 BPB (best=2.18). Next: try attention backward WITH attn_down preserved, or try larger hidden dim."}
